subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes. Head—body 400-590 mm, tail 55-84 mm, ear 80-90 mm, hindfoot 96-110 mm; weight 2.2-5 kg. The Burmese Hare is medium-sized and closely resembles the Indian Hare (
L. nigricollis
). Dorsal pelage is reddish gray, mixed with black and grayer on rump. Ventral pelage is white. Ears are rather large with distinct black tips. Tail is black above and white below. Feet vary, being white in Burmese specimens and fulvous in Thailand specimens.
